}}'''2GIS''' is a Russian local search company that develops digital maps and guides of cities in [[Russia]], [[Kazakhstan]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newskaz.ru/regions/20120409/2939118.html|title=Sputnik Казахстан - обновления новостей онлайн 24 часа|last=Sputnik|website=newskaz.ru|language=ru|access-date=2017-05-21}}</ref> [[Italy]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Chile]], [[United Arab Emirates|The UAE]], [[Kyrgyzstan]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://info.2gis.ru/perm/company/news/2gis-v-bishkeke|title=2ГИС в Бишкеке|website=info.2gis.ru|language=ru|access-date=2017-05-21}}</ref> [[Cyprus]] and [[Ukraine]]. Their headquarters are located in [[Novosibirsk]].

As of 2018, according to company data, 2GIS digital maps covered 350 cities in operating countries, processing more than 2,2 million search queries daily.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://info.2gis.ae/dubai?utm_source=2gis4online&utm_medium=about_link&utm_campaign=start|title=Everything about 2GIS: news, products and business opportunities|website=info.2gis.ae|language=ru|access-date=2018-07-12}}</ref> Also company claims a global audience of more than 40 million monthly users.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://customers.microsoft.com/ru-ru/story/2gis-professional-services-asp-net-core|title=Major local search company develops ad service with open-source technologies and ASP.NET Core in two months|work=Microsoft Customers Stories|access-date=2018-07-12|language=ru-ru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ad.2gis.ae/dubai|title=Advertising in Dubai. Sharjah. Ajman — 2GIS|website=ad.2gis.ae|language=ru|access-date=2018-07-12}}</ref> According to [[Forbes]], 2GIS is one of the largest internet-based companies in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbes.ru/reitingi-photogallery/251148-10-krupneishikh-internet-kompanii-rossii-reiting-forbes/photo/8|title=10 крупнейших интернет-компаний России: рейтинг Forbes|website=forbes.ru|access-date=2017-05-21}}</ref>

All versions of the application are free of charge, and the company's main source of income is advertising on their website. Digital maps come in three versions: PC, Web and Mobile, including iOS and Android platforms.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://info.2gis.ae/dubai/products|title=Download Dubai. Sharjah. Ajman map for free: buildings, companies, routes — 2GIS|website=info.2gis.ae|language=ru|access-date=2018-07-12}}</ref>

In 2013, the company earned 3 billion [[Russian ruble|rubles]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.the-village.ru/village/hopesandfears/story/155855-2gis|title=2ГИС: Зачем лидер рынка геоинформации в России продаёт франшизы по всему миру|work=The Village|access-date=2017-05-21}}</ref> [[Mashable]] included 2GIS in its list of Russia's “20 hottest startups".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mashable.com/2013/11/14/russia-startups/|title=The 20 Hottest Startups in Russia|last=Munford|first=Monty|work=Mashable|access-date=2018-07-12|language=en}}</ref>

In 2015, company raised $40 million from two major investment funds, [[Baring Vostok Capital Partners]] and Ru-Net, to expand its presence in the European part of Russia, to extend a foreign franchises network, as well as to develop new products, stated Vera Garmash, 2GIS President.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ewdn.com/2015/11/04/local-search-and-city-navigation-service-2gis-secures-40-million-to-expand-in-russia-and-internationally/|title=Local search and city navigation service 2GIS secures $40 million to expand in Russia and internationally|date=2015-11-04|work=East-West Digital News|access-date=2018-07-12|language=en-US}}</ref>

In 2016, the [[The Wall Street Journal|Wall Street Journal]] named 2GIS as a recognized Russian startup targeting global markets amid Russian economic crisis and Western sanctions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-venture-capital-funds-look-abroad-1466529651|title=Russia’s Venture-Capital Funds Look Abroad|last=Razumovskaya|first=Olga|date=2016-06-21|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2018-07-12|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kuznech.com/russias-venture-capital-funds-look-abroad/|title=Russia's Venture-Capital Funds Look Abroad {{!}} Kuznech|website=kuznech.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-12}}</ref>

In 2018, [[Government of Dubai]] and 2GIS signed an agreement to improve maps and navigation in Dubai Now — application allowing the city's residents to access government services.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mediaoffice.ae/en/media-center/news/26/3/2018/dubainow.aspx|title= Dubai News|website=mediaoffice.ae|access-date=2018-07-12}}</ref>

